# Conventional Commits

Every commit message must follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/).

## Format

```
<type>[optional scope]: <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer(s)]
```

- **type** (required): `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `perf`, `test`, `build`, `ci`, `chore`, `revert`, etc.
- **scope** (optional): area in parentheses, e.g. `feat(blog): add RSS link`
- **description** (required): imperative mood, lowercase, no period at the end, ~50 chars or less when practical
- Use **BREAKING CHANGE:** in the footer or `!` after type/scope for breaking changes

## Examples

```
feat: add dark mode toggle
fix(posts): correct frontmatter date parsing
docs: update README install steps
chore: bump next to 14.2
```

## Do not use

- Vague messages: `update`, `fixes`, `wip`, `misc`
- Non-conventional prefixes that are not the standard type list unless the project explicitly adopts them

When proposing or running `git commit`, write the full message in this form.
